 way to end a romantic meal and is perfect for couples who love chocolate. Breakfast in bed: This is a great way to start Valentine’s Day off on the right foot. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1978038 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines-419x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1827" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines-419x598.jpg 419w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines-168x240.jpg 168w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines-336x480.jpg 336w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines-420x600.jpg 420w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/valentines.jpg 564w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> The list can go on to include: Ultimately, the best meal for Valentine’s Day is one that is made with love and enjoyed together. So, whether it’s a fancy dinner or a simple meal cooked at home, the most important thing is that it’s shared with your loved one.